==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Escuage
<hw>Es"cu*age</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>escuage</ets>, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧cuage</ets>, from OF.
<ets>escu</ets> shield, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧cu</ets>. See
<er>Esquire</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Feud. Law)</fld> <def>Service of the
shield, a species of knight service by which a tenant was bound to
follow his lord to war, at his own charge. It was afterward exchanged
for a pecuniary satisfaction. Called also
<altname>scutage</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Esculapian</ent>⟦br⟧
